# Implementation Plan: Update Staff Names in config.json from att.docx

We need to update the staff names in `config.json` using the biometric attendance document `input/att.docx` as the main source of truth. This ensures that the auto-calculation script `parse.js` maps employee names exactly without relying on fuzzy matching or throwing warnings.

---

## User Review Required

Please review and confirm the proposed name mapping and how to handle formatting below:

### 1. Spacing Style Options
Biometric system exports often contain multiple spaces between words (e.g., `"Hasan   Mahmud"` instead of `"Hasan Mahmud"`). We can update names in `config.json` in one of two ways:
* **Option A (Exact Copy):** Update names exactly as written in `att.docx` including multiple spaces (e.g. `"Hasan   Mahmud"`, `"Sadia   Sultana  Rima"`). This guarantees exact 1-to-1 matching.
* **Option B (Clean Spacing):** Keep standard single-spacing but match spelling and full names (e.g. `"Hasan Mahmud"`, `"Nusrat Jahan Ira"`, `"Mohoshina Shifa Buble"`). The parser's `normalize()` helper strips all spacing anyway, so this will still match perfectly.

> [!TIP]
> **Recommendation:** We recommend **Option B** (Clean Spacing) because it keeps the final payroll spreadsheets (`Monthly-All`, bank statement, and WhatsApp slips) looking neat and professional while still achieving perfect name matching.

